Class Vector3f

java.lang.Object
tage.rml.Vector3f
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Vector3>, Vector3
public final class Vector3f extends Object implements Vector3
An immutable single-precision floating point 3-component column vector.

This means the input float[] { 1, 2, 3 }; produces the following 

 1
 2
 3

The implementation assumes the input arrays have enough elements to build the vector. When the input array does not have enough elements, an IndexOutOfBoundsException will be thrown. However, when the input array has extra elements, the extra data are ignored.

Author:
Raymond L. Rivera
